1
00:00:01,418 --> 00:00:03,044
(creaking)

2
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:05,171
(light music)

3
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:13,763
SUNWOO: It's a test shot.

4
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:15,223
(camera shutter clicks)

5
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:17,017
EUNSOO: How is it?

6
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,226
Do I look pretty?

7
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:19,728
You look like yourself.

8
00:00:20,812 --> 00:00:22,188
So I do look pretty.

9
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:25,734
Ready.

10
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:27,610
(camera beeps, shutter clicks)

11
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:30,321
SUNWOO: Anyway, stop taking
your ID photos here.

12
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:31,865
-This isn't a photo studio.
-(camera shutter clicks)

13
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:35,660
It's better than a photo studio.
Why would I go and pay someone else

14
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,620
EUNSOO: when my friend makes a living
with photography?

15
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:40,498
-You don't pay me either.
-But I let you hang out with me.

16
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,085
I've been saying it for the past 20 years.
Just let me hang out by myself.

17
00:00:44,169 --> 00:00:45,795
EUNSOO: To be accurate, 19 years.

18
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:49,215
We started hanging out
since we were nine years old.

19
00:00:49,674 --> 00:00:50,508
(sighs)

20
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:52,635
(camera shutter clicks)

21
00:00:54,804 --> 00:00:55,889
SUNWOO: Ready.

22
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:57,724
Okay.

23
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:05,065
(camera beeps, shutter clicks)

24
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:07,275
(theme music)

25
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:33,843
EPISODE 1

26
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:35,220
EUNSOO: You know,

27
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:38,389
all your photos are so somber.

28
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:41,017
-SUNWOO: Why?
-EUNSOO: I'm not sure.

29
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:45,271
EUNSOO: This is just a picture of a puppy,
but it's sad.

30
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:48,483
And this is just a picture of a tree...

31
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,734
(sucks teeth)

32
00:01:50,026 --> 00:01:51,653
...but it's somber for some reason.

33
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:54,572
That just means you've gotten old.

34
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,075
(wheels rattle)

35
00:01:57,784 --> 00:02:01,663
Old enough to relate
to the captured emotion or the moment.

36
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:04,415
Mm-hm.

37
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,709
Did you take these with a film camera too?

38
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:08,545
SUNWOO: Yeah. All of those there.

39
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:09,546
(exclaims)

40
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:14,968
There are so many great digital cameras.
Why do you insist on film?

41
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:19,722
You can review the same shot
a hundred times on a digital camera,

42
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:23,434
but with film, you only get one chance
to capture the moment.

43
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:25,687
I like the significance of singularity.

44
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:27,605
(exclaims, chuckles)

45
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,607
Pretty deep, Han Sunwoo.

46
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:33,069
I guess your exhibition is going to be
another sold-out show, Mr. Han.

47
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:34,988
All done.

48
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:36,322
(sighs)

49
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,492
EUNSOO: My, look.

50
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:41,369
What?

51
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,497
I'm way too pretty.

52
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:45,623
What...

53
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:50,920
This is why I keep coming to you.
You always get my best angles.

54
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:51,838
This is amazing.

55
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:57,886
What is this?

56
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:58,887
Is this yours?

57
00:02:59,387 --> 00:03:01,014
How old are you?

58
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:02,765
(chuckles)

59
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:04,684
Please don't touch my stuff.

60
00:03:05,643 --> 00:03:09,439
Oh, right. You still have the pictures
we took from our trip last year, right?

61
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:12,233
-Why?
-My mom deleted the pictures by accident.

62
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:14,819
But I don't have them either.
Send them together with these.

63
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,779
I don't have them.
I delete pictures right away.

64
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:18,323
EUNSOO: Try looking for them, at least.

65
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:22,452
Geez... I really don't have those
pictures. I deleted them to make space.

66
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:27,540
You probably put them away
in some folder and forgot.

67
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:31,169
Didn't you say you have a meeting
with a composer? Aren't you running late?

68
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:33,046
I did, what time is it?

69
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:34,839
(yelps)

70
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:37,550
Oh, no!

71
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:40,511
-Hey, Sunwoo! How do I look?
-What?

72
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:41,846
-Looking great.
-(mouse clicks)

73
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:42,805
(sucks teeth)

74
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:45,516
Look before you answer.

75
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,268
So pretty.

76
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,395
I'm out. Look for those pictures!

77
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,773
(running footsteps)

78
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:53,858
(Eunsoo grunting)

79
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,444
-Hey, Eunsoo.
-Hey. Good to see you too.

80
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:59,530
Yeah, it was good seeing you!

81
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:02,075
(mouse clicks)

82
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:05,745
(vehicle honking)

83
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:09,999
(music fades)

84
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:36,985
(door clanks open)

85
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:41,281
My bad, did you wait long?
The recording took longer than expected.

86
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:43,241
Not at all. I just arrived too.

87
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:44,242
(exhales)

88
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,410
Try this.

89
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:47,495
WOOIL: It's really good.

90
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:49,580
JEJU MANDARIN JUICE

91
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:51,833
(chuckles)
Please sit. Why are you standing?

92
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,084
(Eunsoo in English)
Oh, okay.

93
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:55,503
(Wooil gulps, exhales)

94
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,714
(in Korean) Thanks for your work.

95
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,716
I bet you couldn't even sleep.

96
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:04,762
Oh, not at all. I'm wired to fall asleep
anywhere I rest my head.

97
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:07,765
I'm not narcoleptic or anything but...

98
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,975
(smack lips)

99
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:10,852
Anyway, I don't feel...

100
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:15,064
too tired these days.

101
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:18,901
Okay. I took a look at your draft.

102
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,237
How was it?

103
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,198
Eunsoo, have you ever experienced
unrequited love?

104
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:25,992
Why do you ask?

105
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:27,869
WOOIL: The lyrics aren't bad.

106
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,912
Mm-hm. The refrain is good.

107
00:05:30,913 --> 00:05:31,831
But...

108
00:05:32,915 --> 00:05:34,208
it's just too lighthearted.

109
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,044
(reflective guitar music)

110
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,087
It doesn't feel real.

111
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:41,507
Ah...

112
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:48,097
The pain and sorrow of not being able
to be with the one you love.

113
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:49,807
(breathes deeply)

114
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,642
Have you never felt anything
like that before?

115
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:57,231
Uh...
(chuckles awkwardly)

116
00:05:57,815 --> 00:05:58,941
All right.
(clears throat)

117
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:03,529
We have three minutes in a song
to inspire people.

118
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:09,160
Even a single photograph needs to convey
and invoke emotion to be received as art.

119
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:14,248
How can we inspire people with our song
when it doesn't convey any real emotion?

120
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:16,209
WOOIL: Don't you agree?

121
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:18,419
Ah...

122
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:20,088
You're right.

123
00:06:21,672 --> 00:06:24,967
Thank you for your hard work anyway.
It's a shame, but we have no choice.

124
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:28,304
It's Jay Jun's new single,
and we can't delay anymore.

125
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:32,642
When I have something else for you,
I'll let you know.

126
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,852
I have to get to my next appointment.
Please excuse me.

127
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:37,271
Please wait! Mr. Kang!

128
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,485
One moment, please.

129
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:45,405
(light music)

130
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:51,077
(Donghyun sighs)

131
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:54,580
What do you mean? Postpone the exhibition?

132
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,249
(breathes deeply)

133
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:00,586
I've been thinking about it,
and this is for the best, Donghyeon.

134
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:03,714
Wow.
(sighs)

135
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,676
The horoscopes are on point today.

136
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:09,178
"You will be shocked by unexpected news."

137
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:14,559
You've worked on this for a whole year.
And now you want to start from scratch?

138
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,352
(grunts)

139
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:18,438
-Hold up.
-(chair thuds)

140
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:20,022
(grunting)

141
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,525
(Donghyeon munching, groaning)

142
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:23,985
(Donghyeon sighs)

143
00:07:24,068 --> 00:07:26,904
DONGHYEON: At least tell me why.
Why are you doing this all of a sudden?

144
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:32,034
Your photographs... really are so good!

145
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,286
What's the problem?

146
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,538
(inhales)

147
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:37,165
I just feel like an impostor.

148
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:39,834
It all feels fake.

149
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:42,211
(light music continues)

150
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,130
(sighs)

151
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:46,883
I see.

152
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:48,384
Mm...

153
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,971
Sunwoo, every budding artist
goes through the same phase.

154
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:53,890
So I totally understand.

155
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:57,018
But think about it.
You were like this last time too.

156
00:07:57,101 --> 00:08:00,354
You said it wasn't ready,
but it was a huge success. Remember?

157
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:03,733
(laughing awkwardly)

158
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:05,902
It was a huge success!

159
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:07,737
It's different from last time.

160
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:11,282
I can't even look at my own photographs.

161
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:13,534
And you want me to present that
to the people?

162
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:14,744
I can't do that.

163
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:16,621
No. I won't.

164
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,417
Can I just take a break for a while?

165
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:22,960
(exhales sharply)

166
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:24,962
SUNWOO: I don't think
I can go on like this.

167
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:27,632
I'm sorry.

168
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:29,842
(sighs)

169
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,470
(cellphone buzzing)

170
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,431
DONGHYEON: Well, Sunwoo.

171
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,141
EUNSOO: Getting started
without you, hurry.

172
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,227
DONGHYEON: Let's just calm down

173
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:41,562
and think about...

174
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,607
I'm going to get going.
I'll see you at home.

175
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:45,733
No, see me here, Sunwoo!

176
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:48,277
Hey, Sunwoo! I'm going to faint!

177
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:51,405
You think I'm joking? Hey, Sunwoo!

178
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,991
(breathes heavily)

179
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,326
Sunwoo...

180
00:08:56,452 --> 00:08:57,286
(exhales sharply)

181
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,668
(cheeky music)

182
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:14,971
MARRIED COUPLE

183
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,138
SUNWOO: It's freezing.

184
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,765
Hey, Mr. Han!

185
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:19,934
-It's been a while, Mari.
-Welcome, Sunwoo.

186
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:21,769
Hey, she's over there.

187
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:25,398
-Rolled omelet to Table Two, Mari.
-Coming.

188
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:26,607
Go talk to her.

189
00:09:26,691 --> 00:09:28,776
I think she got rejected again. Go.

190
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,494
Drinking on an empty stomach again?

191
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:40,121
(groaning)

192
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,622
Oh, you're here.

193
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:44,625
(sighs)

194
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,837
-EUNSOO: Sunwoo.
-Yeah?

195
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:52,425
Do you know anything
about unrequited love?

196
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:55,094
That's out of the blue.

197
00:09:55,469 --> 00:09:57,471
He says that my lyrics lack authenticity

198
00:09:58,514 --> 00:10:01,601
and are utterly devoid of emotions.

199
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:02,560
(Sunwoo sucks teeth)

200
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:04,687
So the lyrics are
about unrequited love this time.

201
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:07,273
-It's so frustrating.
-(crockery clangs)

202
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:10,443
I poured my heart out into those lyrics.
What's so special about unrequited love?

203
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:14,280
If you feel fuzzy, if you like him,
if you miss him, then just ask him out!

204
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:15,489
It's that simple.

205
00:10:15,573 --> 00:10:18,743
Why does unrequited love
have to be so sad and painful?

206
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:21,454
-(slams table)
-I'd say...

207
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,082
it's more like stupid than unrequited.

208
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:26,375
(exhales)

209
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:29,920
EUNSOO: Did I just rhyme?
I should write it down.

210
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:31,297
(breathes deeply)

211
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:34,592
I'm writing it down. Unrequited...

212
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:36,927
(sighs)

213
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:38,054
Stupid...
(clicks tongue)

214
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:43,017
So, they rejected your lyrics
this time too?

215
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,646
Yes, for now.

216
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:50,858
What do you mean, for now?

217
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:54,445
I begged him.

218
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:56,197
One moment, please.

219
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,114
(whimsical music)

220
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:58,032
(Eunsoo exclaims)

221
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:01,827
Can you please give me one more chance?

222
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:04,497
I'll have it quickly revised.

223
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:06,415
Eunsoo,

224
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:10,586
Emotions aren't something that can be
expressed just by thinking hard about it.

225
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:12,672
Let's do a different project another time.

226
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:14,173
I know!

227
00:11:14,256 --> 00:11:15,424
-I know.
-(sighs)

228
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:19,136
I know. I really get it now.

229
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,514
Uh... mm...

230
00:11:22,431 --> 00:11:23,349
EUNSOO: Oh...

231
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:26,102
Two weeks.

232
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:28,729
Just give me two weeks...

233
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,817
and I will show you.

234
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:35,903
(exhales sharply)

235
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,197
Please.

236
00:11:39,365 --> 00:11:43,202
Hey. Write your lyrics in your own style.
There's no need to beg.

237
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:44,787
It isn't the only song in the world.

238
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:47,415
Yep. That song, there's only one of it.

239
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:48,833
(Eunsoo sighs)

240
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,753
He was the one person
I wanted to be acknowledged by.

241
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:55,798
-What's so great about that guy?
-He sure is great!

242
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:58,634
He isn't the only composer in the world.

243
00:11:58,718 --> 00:11:59,844
Hey.

244
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:01,095
(shushes)

245
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:04,807
You can hear his song now.

246
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:07,476
(romantic music playing)

247
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:19,447
-♪ You did well today ♪
-(Eunsoo humming)

248
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:23,117
-♪ The words I wanted to hear ♪
-(Mari laughing)

249
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,160
(thuds)

250
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:29,874
-♪ Actually, I don't know... ♪
-(breathes deeply, exhales)

251
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:31,292
(slams table)

252
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,711
I'm going to get it this time,
no matter what.

253
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:38,215
This is a chance to start a new life
after three years as a nameless lyricist,

254
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:41,051
and get closer to this composer.

255
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:42,470
Good luck.

256
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:46,807
So what is it about unrequited love
that's so sad?

257
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:50,978
To love one person with all your heart!
How awesome is that?

258
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:54,273
-Seriously, I don't get it.
-(breathes deeply)

259
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:57,443
The sad part is
not being able to do anything about it.

260
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,112
It's my own heart.

261
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:04,825
Yet I have no control over how I feel.
Nothing goes according to my volition.

262
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:10,831
-But isn't love the same?
-Love, you can spit out, at least.

263
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:15,294
But when it's one-sided,
you have to swallow it and keep it in.

264
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:18,714
(sighs deeply)

265
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,050
What?

266
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,763
How would you know that?

267
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:27,807
Like you have experience.

268
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:32,895
(exclaims)

269
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:36,482
One doesn't need to...

270
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,026
Sunwoo...

271
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:44,990
You fell for a girl in the States,
didn't you?

272
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:47,785
-So, is she an American? Latina?
-Wow.

273
00:13:47,868 --> 00:13:51,413
What's her name?
Jennifer? Sofia? Elizabeth? What is it?

274
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,456
Yeah. It's Jennifer.

275
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,291
Jennifer...

276
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,168
(sighs)
I could use a drink.

277
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,629
(liquid pours)

278
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:01,298
I'm so jealous.

279
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:04,510
Gosh.

280
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:07,638
-♪ A heart of love has only become ♪
-(Sunwoo sighs)

281
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:11,642
-♪ A puzzle to solve ♪
-(Sunwoo slurps)

282
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:16,397
♪ A channel for pain ♪

283
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:17,523
It's snowing.

284
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:22,152
♪ The smaller I feel ♪

285
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:25,573
-♪ I want to comfort ♪
-It's pretty.

286
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:28,868
♪ And stand up for myself ♪

287
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:30,160
(clicks tongue, sighs)

288
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:31,871
-Sunwoo.
-Yeah?

289
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,124
When did you say
you were leaving Korea again?

290
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:37,459
Me? In two weeks.

291
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:39,253
Why?

292
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:41,797
Do you want to live with me,
just for two weeks?

293
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:44,383
(inhales)
What are you talking about?

294
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:48,721
(indistinct chattering)

295
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:51,223
Come live with me, and be my assistant.

296
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:52,683
(scoffs)

297
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,811
Help me write lyrics.

298
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:57,813
(chuckles)

299
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,315
No.

300
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:01,066
Why not?

301
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,652
-Your place is a pigsty.
-It's gotten a lot cleaner.

302
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,362
-Still no.
-Why not?

303
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:08,032
-It's probably still a mess.
-I'll clean it all up!

304
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:10,951
I have to finish writing the lyrics
in two weeks, and I don't have time.

305
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:14,079
Donghyeon's place is a studio apartment.
My place is more spacious.

306
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,665
I'm a photographer, not a lyricist.
Forget it.

307
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:19,001
But you know something that I don't.

308
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:22,171
The sorrow that you feel for Jennifer.

309
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:24,882
(soft music)

310
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,009
What do you say?

311
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,512
-(breathes deeply)
-EUNSOO: Yes?

312
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:35,559
(soft music continues)

313
00:15:36,226 --> 00:15:37,978
-Nope.
-Please!

314
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:39,980
No.

315
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:42,066
SUNWOO: Gyeolhan!

316
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,234
Hey!

317
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,569
(Eunsoo wailing)

318
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:50,324
EUNSOO: My lyrics lack emotion...

319
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:57,081
-(wailing)
-Hey, you're going to trip.

320
00:15:57,539 --> 00:15:58,832
-(vehicle approaching)
-Geez.

321
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,709
-(honking)
-(engine revs)

322
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:03,295
Come on!

323
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,339
-Seriously...
-What's wrong with that guy?

324
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,007
What was that?

325
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,802
(wails)

326
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:15,557
What do I do now?
I know nothing about unrequited love!

327
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:22,147
I tell guys if I like them,
and they like me when I like them,

328
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:27,319
so how am I supposed know
about that sadness?

329
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,488
(reflective music)

330
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:31,573
And why is it so cold tonight?

331
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,994
It's cold since you're dressed so lightly.

332
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:36,870
Hey, come here.

333
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:40,165
-You know,
-Yes?

334
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:42,918
I'm worse than Three-Minute Curry.

335
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:48,465
Three-Minute Curry can win
over people's tastes in three minutes,

336
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:52,219
but my lyrics can't.

337
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,679
(grunts)

338
00:16:54,763 --> 00:16:57,141
Call me Curry from now on.

339
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,269
It's only right.

340
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:02,521
(chuckles)

341
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:05,232
You really drive me crazy.

342
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:07,943
(groans)

343
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:09,987
(wails)

344
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,406
EUNSOO: Wait up.

345
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,576
Gosh, my head hurts.

346
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:16,618
(Sunwoo sighs)

347
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:19,079
-SUNWOO: I knew you'd be like this.
-EUNSOO: Huh?

348
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:21,123
-EUNSOO: Hey, hurry!
-SUNWOO: Wait!

349
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,543
(pants, gasps)

350
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:27,129
EUNSOO: It's a claw machine!

351
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,714
(sniffles)

352
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,510
If I get you a prize here,
will you come to my house?

353
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,512
-What?
-You like stuffed animals, right?

354
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:37,931
-No.
-All right. I got this.

355
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:40,225
I know you like stuffed animals...

356
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,855
Let's go if you don't have cash.

357
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:48,776
So you do.

358
00:17:50,027 --> 00:17:51,278
(machine whirring)

359
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:52,613
Come on!

360
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:54,198
(smack lips)

361
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:57,451
(machine whirs, beeps)

362
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:01,455
EUNSOO: This is it.

363
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,831
(machine whirring, clanking)

364
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:04,083
This should do it.

365
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,835
-(emotive music)
-(machine whirring)

366
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:10,255
-Looks good.
-EUNSOO: Go.

367
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:12,341
Go...

368
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,386
(machine beeps)

369
00:18:18,138 --> 00:18:21,058
SUNWOO: Try to lift the heavy side.

370
00:18:21,141 --> 00:18:22,309
-Okay.
-Yes.

371
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:23,894
-Right here.
-Good.

372
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,063
SUNWOO: Good.

373
00:18:27,689 --> 00:18:29,566
-Go. Go!
-Good.

374
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:32,945
(sucks teeth)

375
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:35,989
-Sir! This ate my coins!
-SUNWOO: No, it's working. Never mind!

376
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:38,367
-EUNSOO: I can get it with my hands.
-SUNWOO: Hey, stop.

377
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:41,078
-SUNWOO: You shouldn't do that, stop.
-EUNSOO: It's okay, I've done this before.

378
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:44,081
-I've done this before, I really have!
-SUNWOO: Okay, I'll just buy you one.

379
00:18:44,164 --> 00:18:44,998
Damn it...

380
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:50,003
EUNSOO: Sorry.

381
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:53,632
You must be busy
preparing for your exhibition.

382
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:59,304
I'll send you the biggest standing wreath.

383
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:01,682
You have to put it right at the entrance.

384
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,768
I decided to postpone the exhibition.

385
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:06,895
What?

386
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:10,065
I want to start over from the beginning.

387
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:13,277
What did you not like about it?

388
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:18,699
Everything feels like a lie.

389
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:22,703
Nowadays, I don't even know
what to take photographs of,

390
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:26,165
and even when I do,
it just doesn't feel genuine.

391
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,334
(sighs)

392
00:19:32,379 --> 00:19:35,132
It's for the best.
It's better than feeling sketchy.

393
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:38,635
Don't worry about me,
and worry about yourself.

394
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:43,515
Watch some romance movies and dramas.

395
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:45,642
You know nothing about unrequited love

396
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:49,813
because you only watch movies
about revenge or flesh-eating zombies.

397
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:52,941
(soft music)

398
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:58,030
So who is it?

399
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,534
-What do you mean?
-Your crush.

400
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:04,786
-Show me her picture.
-I don't have one.

401
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:08,290
-Yes, you do! Let me see!
-I'm telling you, I don't! Gosh.

402
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:11,210
I know you have it.

403
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:12,711
What's up with you today?

404
00:20:12,794 --> 00:20:14,713
Okay, then.

405
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:19,885
Well, don't let her get to you, Sunwoo.

406
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:24,056
If she rejects you, come to me.

407
00:20:25,849 --> 00:20:26,808
To you?

408
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:28,227
Yes.

409
00:20:30,687 --> 00:20:34,233
Your best friend of 20 years
will buy you a drink.

410
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:36,360
(chuckles)

411
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,405
(light music)

412
00:20:41,156 --> 00:20:42,658
To be accurate, 19 years.

413
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:46,954
Hurry up!
(chuckles)

414
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:59,508
You don't have to walk me home.

415
00:21:02,427 --> 00:21:04,263
Get going. It's late.

416
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:07,849
Wash up before you go to bed.
Don't just fall asleep on a couch.

417
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:08,976
Okay, Mom.

418
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:14,189
Sunwoo.

419
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,235
Be honest about how you feel.

420
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:20,946
Then your photographs
will look sincere too.

421
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:25,617
Do what you want to do
and follow your heart,

422
00:21:26,576 --> 00:21:28,704
in order to take good photographs.

423
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:32,666
Look at me suffering as I try to write
about something I don't understand.

424
00:21:32,749 --> 00:21:33,792
(chuckles)

425
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,213
So hurry up and tell your Jennifer
how you feel.

426
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,590
Be honest with her, okay?

427
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,219
It's freezing. I'm going inside.

428
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,220
Get inside.

429
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:47,180
-I'm going in. See you!
-Bye.

430
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:49,266
(running footsteps)

431
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:57,607
(groans, exhales)

432
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:02,654
(sighs)
Seriously, my couch is the best.

433
00:22:06,366 --> 00:22:07,242
(sighs)

434
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,123
(music fades)

435
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:18,003
(exhales sharply)

436
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:19,087
Sunwoo.

437
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,300
What are you holding onto?

438
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:30,140
(exhales)

439
00:22:30,557 --> 00:22:32,726
(light music)

440
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:37,064
(cellphone buzzing)

441
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:42,861
EUNSOO: Washed up.

442
00:22:46,448 --> 00:22:47,407
(cellphone buzzing)

443
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:50,494
DONGHYEON: My girlfriend
just came over to my place.

444
00:22:50,744 --> 00:22:53,288
Can you spend the night
in your workroom just for tonight?

445
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:54,498
I'm really sorry.

446
00:22:56,124 --> 00:22:58,293
(light music continues)

447
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:07,719
(sighs)

448
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:09,721
(switch clacks)

449
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:22,192
(light music)

450
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:29,574
(sighs)

451
00:23:37,541 --> 00:23:39,042
EUNSOO: Be honest about how you feel.

452
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:40,961
Then your photographs
will look sincere too.

453
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:45,006
Do what you want to do
and follow your heart,

454
00:23:45,632 --> 00:23:47,801
in order to take good photographs.

455
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:52,013
(keyboard clacks)

456
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:57,644
(keyboard clacks)

457
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:05,527
(keyboard clacking)

458
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:08,530
(exhales sharply)

459
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:15,370
(mouse clicks)

460
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,540
(reflective music)

461
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:21,460
(chuckles softly)

462
00:24:28,341 --> 00:24:30,594
(reflective music continues)

463
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:40,770
4 YEARS AGO

464
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:42,564
(crockery clanging)

465
00:24:43,815 --> 00:24:45,942
Mari! Bring us rice wine on your way!

466
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,402
MARI: Get it yourself!

467
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:48,445
Gosh.

468
00:24:51,448 --> 00:24:53,617
(footsteps thumping)

469
00:24:56,286 --> 00:24:58,622
You said you had something to tell me.
What is it?

470
00:24:58,705 --> 00:24:59,706
(thuds)

471
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:04,127
-Well...
-Hey, this dish turned out great.

472
00:25:04,711 --> 00:25:07,589
-I'll tell you later. After the results.
-Okay.

473
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:08,924
(Gyeolhan exclaiming)

474
00:25:09,007 --> 00:25:12,093
-Make some space for this.
-Is everyone ready?

475
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:14,137
-What is this?
-Look!

476
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:16,389
What do I do? I'm so nervous.

477
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:17,891
Why are you getting nervous?

478
00:25:17,974 --> 00:25:21,102
You said this is the biggest contest
in the country, right?

479
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:23,021
Then the prize money must be hefty too.

480
00:25:23,104 --> 00:25:24,773
Should we bring out some expensive dishes?

481
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:28,527
Of course. He made it to the final three.
He's gotta be first place.

482
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:30,237
-Hey.
-She's right.

483
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,365
Here it is. The winning entries.

484
00:25:33,448 --> 00:25:35,575
-Oh, my gosh!
-Winning entries, here we go.

485
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:37,869
EUNSOO: I'm clicking it.

486
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:39,329
MARI: Please!

487
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:41,915
One, two, three!

488
00:25:47,337 --> 00:25:49,422
EUNSOO: What? Second place?

489
00:25:53,843 --> 00:25:57,514
-(exclaiming, applauding)
-(cheering)

490
00:25:57,597 --> 00:26:01,101
Hey! He made it to the final three
and got second place. That's amazing!

491
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:03,061
-I'm proud of you, Sunwoo!
-Han...

492
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:05,438
-(slams table)
-No way. How can this be?

493
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:07,941
-EUNSOO: How can Sunwoo be second place?
-Hey, sit down.

494
00:26:08,024 --> 00:26:10,402
So who is this guy in first place?

495
00:26:11,528 --> 00:26:12,654
Let me see.

496
00:26:13,446 --> 00:26:16,283
His stuff isn't even that good!
Yours is so much better!

497
00:26:16,366 --> 00:26:18,493
This is outrageous.
I'm going to file a complaint.

498
00:26:18,577 --> 00:26:21,204
-There she goes again.
-I'm okay. Really.

499
00:26:21,913 --> 00:26:24,416
-Let's have a toast.
-Sure, for Sunwoo!

500
00:26:24,541 --> 00:26:27,252
-Congratulations!
-Great.

501
00:26:28,169 --> 00:26:29,879
-But I'm not okay...
-MARI: What was that?

502
00:26:30,005 --> 00:26:31,172
(Gyeolhan laughing)

503
00:26:31,631 --> 00:26:32,757
(exhales)

504
00:26:33,675 --> 00:26:37,220
MARRIED COUPLE

505
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:39,723
-(emotional music playing)
-(crockery clanging)

506
00:26:39,806 --> 00:26:41,516
-♪ Please don't look at me ♪
-Han Sunwoo.

507
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:45,562
-♪ With eyes I do not recognize ♪
-Don't you get dispirited.

508
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:47,939
I'll kick your butt
if you let anyone do that to you.

509
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:49,190
♪ All I need is your love... ♪

510
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:51,359
You're the only one who's dispirited here.

511
00:26:52,235 --> 00:26:53,194
(chuckles)

512
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,655
-♪ I want to be happy ♪
-Oh, no.

513
00:26:55,739 --> 00:26:58,241
-Another song about a breakup.
-♪ I don't want to cry anymore... ♪

514
00:26:58,325 --> 00:27:01,119
-Mari, do something about that music.
-Kill it.

515
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:03,955
-♪ I wish we could go back ♪
-There she goes again.

516
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:07,417
♪ To how we used to be... ♪

517
00:27:08,835 --> 00:27:09,836
EUNSOO: Hey.

518
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:11,755
What are you looking at?

519
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:14,257
Nothing.

520
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,093
Man, isn't it hot?

521
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:20,430
-Want to get some fresh air?
-No.

522
00:27:22,098 --> 00:27:24,559
Stop drinking. You're going to get drunk.

523
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:27,937
Let her be so she can forget.

524
00:27:28,563 --> 00:27:31,691
What is there to cry over about a guy
who cheated on you?

525
00:27:32,567 --> 00:27:35,445
-He was so handsome.
-Handsome, my butt.

526
00:27:35,695 --> 00:27:39,741
I didn't like him the moment he picked out
all the carrots from my braised ribs.

527
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:44,329
Frankly, if anyone is handsome,
it's our Sunwoo.

528
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:45,664
He's right!

529
00:27:45,747 --> 00:27:51,252
Don't date scumbags like your ex,
and date guys like him.

530
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:53,588
No, just date Sunwoo!

531
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,131
MARI: Stop wasting your time on duds.

532
00:27:56,383 --> 00:27:57,300
Sunwoo?

533
00:27:59,636 --> 00:28:00,595
(slurps)

534
00:28:01,012 --> 00:28:03,139
-No, not him.
-MARI: Why not?

535
00:28:03,473 --> 00:28:05,642
You've known him for 15 years.
He's verified!

536
00:28:06,017 --> 00:28:07,143
(sighs, smack lips)

537
00:28:07,227 --> 00:28:09,354
Because we can never break up.

538
00:28:10,271 --> 00:28:14,150
If we don't want to ever break up,
we have to remain friends forever.

539
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:19,322
I miss even a bastard like my ex.

540
00:28:19,406 --> 00:28:23,034
If we date and ever break up,
then how am I supposed to live? I can't.

541
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:24,619
Right, Sunwoo?

542
00:28:25,537 --> 00:28:27,122
Let's never break up.

543
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:29,416
(Sunwoo chuckles)

544
00:28:30,458 --> 00:28:32,419
-(glass clinks)
-(Gyeolhan exclaims)

545
00:28:33,002 --> 00:28:34,379
What a friendship.

546
00:28:34,462 --> 00:28:35,922
Goodness.

547
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:41,636
(reflective music)

548
00:28:43,388 --> 00:28:45,890
(mouse clicking)

549
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,409
(reflective music continues)

550
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:13,585
(music fades)

551
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:23,636
(knocking on door)

552
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:30,351
(knocking on door continues)

553
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:31,978
(gasps)

554
00:29:33,229 --> 00:29:35,565
-(knocking on door)
-EUNSOO: I'm coming.

555
00:29:38,651 --> 00:29:40,195
(sighs, groans)

556
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:42,197
-(door beeps)
-Who is it?

557
00:29:43,198 --> 00:29:44,532
What took you so long?

558
00:29:46,034 --> 00:29:48,036
(birds chirping)

559
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:51,748
What is this?

560
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:53,708
What do you think?
It's cold. Let's go inside.

561
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:54,918
(groans)

562
00:29:55,001 --> 00:29:56,836
(exhales sharply, grunts)

563
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:59,881
-EUNSOO: What's up? You didn't even call.
-SUNWOO: You didn't pick up.

564
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:01,674
(exhales sharply)

565
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:03,510
And what's this?

566
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:06,137
-My clothes.
-Are you going somewhere?

567
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,055
Yes.

568
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:08,389
Here.

569
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:09,307
Here?

570
00:30:09,808 --> 00:30:12,060
-You told me to come.
-EUNSOO: I did?

571
00:30:13,436 --> 00:30:15,021
You asked me to be your assistant.

572
00:30:15,104 --> 00:30:17,315
Gosh, it was freezing out there.

573
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:19,776
I thought my place was too filthy for you.

574
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:22,028
-(light music)
-(pants)

575
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:25,031
It's gotten a lot better. Great.

576
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:26,449
Huh...

577
00:30:27,450 --> 00:30:28,952
Donghyeon has his girlfriend over.

578
00:30:29,702 --> 00:30:31,287
I got kicked out and have nowhere to go.

579
00:30:31,371 --> 00:30:34,749
♪ The warm sun sets... ♪

580
00:30:36,292 --> 00:30:39,712
You said this song
is your big opportunity, right?

581
00:30:40,088 --> 00:30:41,130
I'll help you.

582
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:42,382
You need me.

583
00:30:42,465 --> 00:30:45,927
♪ If it's okay with you ♪

584
00:30:47,387 --> 00:30:48,513
Welcome, my assistant.

585
00:30:49,138 --> 00:30:52,475
♪ I'll go pick you up ♪

586
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:55,186
♪ How about some coffee? ♪

587
00:30:55,937 --> 00:30:58,773
♪ Anything is fine... ♪

588
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:00,567
-SUNWOO: Are these all lyrics?
-Yes.

589
00:31:00,650 --> 00:31:03,194
-SUNWOO: You don't need these, right?
-EUNSOO: Wait, the brown one!

590
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:04,571
SUNWOO: I'll throw away the rest.

591
00:31:04,946 --> 00:31:05,905
(sighs)

592
00:31:08,116 --> 00:31:10,451
Are you even eating properly?

593
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:14,080
♪ I don't mind if it's awkward ♪

594
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:17,417
-♪ The wind blows ♪
-Here's the trash bin!

595
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:20,128
♪ And makes my heart flutter ♪

596
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:23,256
-Here.
-♪ Ever so gently... ♪

597
00:31:23,339 --> 00:31:25,258
-This one's really sweet.
-Have another.

598
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:28,928
-Isn't it so good?
-♪ I care about you ♪

599
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:31,764
♪ Before I knew it, it seems ♪

600
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:32,807
(Eunsoo grunts)

601
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:36,686
♪ I have fallen for you ♪

602
00:31:38,771 --> 00:31:39,772
EUNSOO: I'll do it myself.

603
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:42,191
-SUNWOO: Is it okay if I throw these away?
-No, I need them!

604
00:31:42,275 --> 00:31:44,944
♪ I don't wanna anything, something ♪

605
00:31:47,196 --> 00:31:48,281
Oh, gosh.

606
00:31:49,532 --> 00:31:52,493
EUNSOO: When did all this happen?

607
00:31:53,328 --> 00:31:55,038
-♪ With you ♪
-(Eunsoo chuckles awkwardly)

608
00:31:55,121 --> 00:31:59,208
-I'll throw out the garbage first.
-♪ We'll shine brighter than any star ♪

609
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:05,757
(sizzling)

610
00:32:06,424 --> 00:32:09,385
(sizzling, fire whooshes)

611
00:32:12,263 --> 00:32:16,434
♪ The warm evening breeze ♪

612
00:32:17,894 --> 00:32:22,273
♪ Softens my heart ♪ 

613
00:32:23,816 --> 00:32:25,735
Okay, I see.

614
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:27,862
-(clears throat)
-Bye.

615
00:32:29,906 --> 00:32:33,368
This is crazy.
Did you learn to cook in the States?

616
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:36,245
-Try some.
-Okay.

617
00:32:39,540 --> 00:32:41,793
(munching)

618
00:32:42,418 --> 00:32:43,461
(groans)

619
00:32:43,962 --> 00:32:45,004
How is it?

620
00:32:46,631 --> 00:32:47,590
This...

621
00:32:49,717 --> 00:32:50,677
needs rice wine.

622
00:32:51,636 --> 00:32:52,553
(Eunsoo yelps)

623
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,305
-EUNSOO: This is amazing. Wow.
-Good choice.

624
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:57,183
Ta-da!

625
00:32:58,559 --> 00:33:02,897
You said grape wines give you headaches,
so why do you still have wine glasses?

626
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,942
Rice wine is wine too.
It's better in a wine glass.

627
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:07,151
Ah...

628
00:33:07,944 --> 00:33:09,529
Let me fill your glass.

629
00:33:09,612 --> 00:33:12,031
-EUNSOO: Here you go.
-Oh, yes.

630
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:15,368
Color looks great.

631
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:19,038
(exclaims)

632
00:33:19,122 --> 00:33:20,623
Perfect. Cheers!

633
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:22,375
(glass clinks)

634
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:26,462
(exclaims)

635
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:28,423
(exhales)

636
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:30,091
-EUNSOO: This is it.
-Mmm.

637
00:33:31,467 --> 00:33:34,512
So how long is Donghyeon's girlfriend
staying with him?

638
00:33:35,471 --> 00:33:36,305
What?

639
00:33:38,224 --> 00:33:39,392
Oh, two weeks.

640
00:33:39,475 --> 00:33:41,853
The timing is really crazy.

641
00:33:42,645 --> 00:33:44,689
-Try some of this too.
-Okay.

642
00:33:45,064 --> 00:33:47,066
(Eunsoo gasps)
And what is this?

643
00:33:49,485 --> 00:33:50,319
(slurps)

644
00:33:52,947 --> 00:33:54,782
EUNSOO: You should be a chef
in your free time.

645
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:56,284
(Eunsoo munching)

646
00:33:56,576 --> 00:33:59,871
I just promoted you
from my assistant to my manager.

647
00:34:00,455 --> 00:34:01,289
Why?

648
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:04,375
Congrats. Cheers.

649
00:34:05,126 --> 00:34:06,002
Oh...

650
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:07,045
(glass clinks)

651
00:34:07,712 --> 00:34:08,921
(breathes deeply)

652
00:34:09,005 --> 00:34:10,381
-(both slurping)
-(Eunsoo sighs)

653
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:12,842
Do you have a mandarin collection?

654
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,094
Please eat some.

655
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:19,807
My mom keeps sending them,
but I just can't have anymore.

656
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:22,477
So how are your parents doing?

657
00:34:23,019 --> 00:34:25,146
-Do they like living on Jeju Island?
-Absolutely.

658
00:34:25,813 --> 00:34:30,443
I get photos of the ocean, of mandarins,
of them eating mandarins by the ocean.

659
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:33,446
Please eat five a day until you leave.

660
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:35,031
Sure.

661
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:37,658
(emotive music)

662
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:39,827
EUNSOO: So do you really not have
a photo of her?

663
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:41,412
SUNWOO: Who?

664
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:43,164
EUNSOO: Your Jennifer.

665
00:34:43,706 --> 00:34:45,083
SUNWOO: I don't have any.

666
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:48,669
EUNSOO: How can you not have a photo
of your crush when you're a photographer?

667
00:34:49,128 --> 00:34:50,838
SUNWOO: I said I'll share
what it feels like

668
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:52,882
to be in unrequited love, not identities.

669
00:34:53,299 --> 00:34:54,425
(Eunsoo scoffs)

670
00:34:54,509 --> 00:34:55,676
EUNSOO: Then at least tell me.

671
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:57,804
Why can't you tell her you like her?

672
00:34:58,387 --> 00:35:00,223
SUNWOO: It's not that I can't.
I choose not to.

673
00:35:00,807 --> 00:35:02,100
EUNSOO: In case you get rejected?

674
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:05,144
SUNWOO: Not getting rejected,
but I'm scared I'd lose her.

675
00:35:05,937 --> 00:35:07,563
EUNSOO: Don't worry too much, my friend.

676
00:35:08,147 --> 00:35:11,234
Who knows? Maybe she likes you too.

677
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:13,486
SUNWOO: How about you?

678
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:15,947
EUNSOO: Huh? What about me?
(munching)

679
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:19,450
Well, is there anyone you're into?

680
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,411
Mm...

681
00:35:23,162 --> 00:35:24,622
(breathes deeply)

682
00:35:24,705 --> 00:35:26,707
(exhaled sharply)

683
00:35:27,041 --> 00:35:29,961
-I don't know.
-What do you mean, you don't know?

684
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,755
-(chuckles)
-(cellphone buzzing)

685
00:35:37,343 --> 00:35:38,177
(Eunsoo gasps)

686
00:35:38,594 --> 00:35:40,471
-It's adorable.
-What is it?

687
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:44,851
It's the composer I mentioned last night.
He took a selfie with a puppy.

688
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:47,061
Look, it's so adorable.

689
00:35:47,478 --> 00:35:48,646
EUNSOO: Like this post.

690
00:35:49,897 --> 00:35:53,693
(gasps)
I think he really likes plants.

691
00:35:53,776 --> 00:35:55,653
Did you know?
Plants can listen to music too.

692
00:35:55,736 --> 00:35:58,531
I think that's the reason
why his plants look so healthy.

693
00:35:58,614 --> 00:35:59,824
Because his music is good.

694
00:36:00,283 --> 00:36:01,367
Oh, wow.

695
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:04,245
He has the same headphones that I use.
How cool is that?

696
00:36:04,328 --> 00:36:05,454
Look. I have the same one.

697
00:36:05,788 --> 00:36:06,622
(gasps)

698
00:36:07,623 --> 00:36:08,457
(glass clinks)

699
00:36:10,084 --> 00:36:12,628
-(Sunwoo gulping)
-Hey, stop drinking alone.

700
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:16,257
(exhales)

701
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:21,512
-(Eunsoo groans)
-(Sunwoo sighs)

702
00:36:23,556 --> 00:36:26,017
Hey, Sunwoo.

703
00:36:26,434 --> 00:36:27,393
What?

704
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:32,607
Why does the ground keep moving?

705
00:36:33,149 --> 00:36:35,318
(munching)

706
00:36:37,945 --> 00:36:38,779
Here, look.

707
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:43,326
SUNWOO: I got it.

708
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:46,787
-SUNWOO: See?
-(chuckles)

709
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:48,706
You're pretty good.

710
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:50,666
EUNSOO: This is great.

711
00:36:51,292 --> 00:36:52,793
(breathes deeply)

712
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:54,712
This is great...
(groans)

713
00:36:56,797 --> 00:36:57,757
(sighs)

714
00:36:58,466 --> 00:37:00,426
Don't sleep on the floor.

715
00:37:01,052 --> 00:37:01,969
Okay.

716
00:37:02,511 --> 00:37:04,805
Come on, go to bed.

717
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,642
EUNSOO: It's so cold...

718
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:09,810
-So cold...
-(sighs)

719
00:37:12,939 --> 00:37:13,856
(gasps)

720
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:22,907
(reflective music)

721
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:28,663
(groans, breathes deeply)

722
00:37:34,919 --> 00:37:37,004
(reflective music continues)

723
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:38,881
(chuckles)

724
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:43,386
(groans)

725
00:37:44,262 --> 00:37:45,346
(sighs)

726
00:37:48,224 --> 00:37:49,141
(grunts)

727
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:50,726
(music fades)

728
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:03,155
(Love Love Love playing)

729
00:38:12,164 --> 00:38:16,085
-♪ I can see myself in your eyes ♪
-(inhales)

730
00:38:16,585 --> 00:38:21,465
-It's freezing.
-♪ Feel me. Embrace me ♪"

731
00:38:22,925 --> 00:38:26,721
-♪ One step at a time, come closer ♪
-Hey.

732
00:38:28,222 --> 00:38:31,183
♪ And just smile for me ♪

733
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:37,565
♪ Love, love, love,
love, love, love, love ♪

734
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:43,321
♪ Everything stops when I look at you... ♪

735
00:38:43,946 --> 00:38:45,072
Stop that.

736
00:38:47,241 --> 00:38:48,993
Just let me be.

737
00:38:49,535 --> 00:38:52,705
-♪ Can you hear the sound of my heart? ♪
-(exhales sharply)

738
00:38:54,707 --> 00:38:59,170
♪ Love, love, love,
love, love, love, love ♪

739
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:04,800
♪ Everything stops when I look at you ♪

740
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:10,222
♪ Love, love, love,
love, love, love, love ♪

741
00:39:10,931 --> 00:39:14,518
♪ Can you hear the sound of my heart? ♪

742
00:39:16,687 --> 00:39:17,646
(music fades)

743
00:39:18,647 --> 00:39:19,482
(birds chirping)

744
00:39:21,150 --> 00:39:22,401
(music stops)

745
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:47,051
(emotive music)

746
00:40:15,996 --> 00:40:18,582
(emotive music continues)

747
00:40:27,925 --> 00:40:30,678
(breathes deeply)

748
00:40:33,931 --> 00:40:35,391
This is crazy.

749
00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:50,865
(emotive music continues)

750
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:24,857
(emotional music playing)

751
00:41:28,861 --> 00:41:31,489
-(approaching footsteps)
-(door opens)

752
00:41:32,239 --> 00:41:33,365
What are you doing?

753
00:41:34,450 --> 00:41:35,701
Just getting some water.

754
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:37,661
Do you want some?

755
00:41:41,207 --> 00:41:42,249
(Eunsoo groans)

756
00:41:45,377 --> 00:41:47,963
You said you had something to tell me.
So what is it?

757
00:41:49,089 --> 00:41:50,174
Nothing.

758
00:41:51,717 --> 00:41:53,844
Don't drink too much.

759
00:41:53,928 --> 00:41:57,223
No, I need to drink more
and vent about losing first place.

760
00:41:57,473 --> 00:41:58,432
Come on in.

761
00:42:02,102 --> 00:42:03,979
GYEOLHAN: Come back to your seat!

762
00:42:08,943 --> 00:42:10,986
(emotional music rises)

763
00:42:22,790 --> 00:42:25,417
(emotional music continues)
